		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The aim of this project is to explore and develop methods for the fabrication of nanotips, with tips radius on the scale <100nm, and to investigate the field emission properties of the tips, with a view to applications in two areas: (i) molecular detection (gas sensing) in the gas phase, via measurements of the electron transport properties of the gas; (ii) analysis of surface chemical composition, by Scanning Probe Energy Loss Spectroscopy (SPELS), with a projected spatial resolution down to ~ 10nm. The project exploits the laboratory's expertise in both nanofabrication and electron scattering.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
